Description:
Renovate and Reinvigorate
Great opportunity for the first home buyer, investor or those looking for a humble solid brick veneer home or investment property they can renovate and style their own way. Positioned in Whittington just a short distance to conveniences, public transport, the Bellarine Hwy and only minutes from the CBD, this 3BR residence needs a little attention to give it the modern makeover that it deserves. The creative buyer has the opportunity to enhance the living areas and functionality of the kitchen which are already brimming with character thanks to a boldly painted interior and floorboards throughout. The home has three bedrooms main with built-in robes, gas heating and is presented on a generous 558sqm (approx.) block with garage & ample parking. Supermarkets, parks, schools, public transport and the popular Bellarine Rail Trail are within easy reach. Inspect today.

Description:
3 bedrooms, 2 living, Study & a Pool!
Nestled away in a quiet court and close to all local amenities, this 3 bedroom brick veneer is suited for all buyers, the opportunities are endless. Situated on a generous 570sqm block.
The light-filled home has 3 spacious bedrooms with built in robes, open plan kitchen/meals, large adjoining living/dining, space to be utilised as a 2nd living room, study/4th bedroom, central bathroom and separate laundry.
Kitchen/meals area with dishwasher, walk in pantry and ample bench space; split a/c in the 2nd living and gas heater. Outside offers a fantastic opportunity to transform the existing in-ground pool area in to an amazing entertaining area. Generous front yarded area, single garage positioned at the rear of the block and an external WC.
In a handy location, there is loads of scope to invest and renovate to your heart's content and enjoy what this property has to offer. Inspect today!

Description:
A Family Entertainer!
You will be absolutely delighted with what you find when you inspect this lovely 4 bedroom home which has so much to offer for the price. Step inside to find 2 separate spacious living areas, master bedroom with WIR & ensuite and BIR's to the 3 other bedrooms. The kitchen with plenty of bench space and dishwasher overlooks the central family room & dining area. With a high roof line and floor to ceiling windows the property has an abundance of natural light.
Year round entertaining can be enjoyed in the huge covered outdoor entertainment area with bistros blinds. Comfort is ensured with two split systems for heating & cooling and you will astonished by the ample amount if storage space. Add to all this a double remote garage with internal access plus garden shed. This home is the complete package and provides easy access to public transport, shopping centres, primary & secondary schools & only 5 minutes to Geelong CBD!

Description:
Exceptional Value - Peaceful Location.
Positioned perfectly at the end of a private cul-de-sac with 'local traffic only' this property represents incredible value and is ideal for the growing family.
With 2 living spaces, 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, kitchen, dining, laundry, alfresco dining and more, you will be astonished by what your money can buy.
The Kitchen is centrally located, includes pantry and gas cooking and provides the chef of the home a full view of all living spaces inside and out. All 4 bedrooms have BIR's and the master has an ensuite. Gas heating and AC control the climate year round.
A substantial outdoor undercover entertaining space opening out from the dining / 2nd living overlooks attractive low maintenance garden beds and established trees. A garden shed is complimented by a potting area / fernery alcove that will excite the family's green thumb and a lock up garage with space for a workshop with full access to the rear yard completes the attributes of the home.
With shops, schools, transport, reserves and more within short walking distance, this is truly one of the best buys in the market. Contact Dion today on 0424 940 629 to take advantage of this incredible opportunity.

Description:
Under Contract
Under clear instructions from the executors of this estate, this well cared for home is offered for sale for the first time in 50 years and is the perfect affordable opportunity for a first home buyer, young family or investor.
This immaculately presented and solidly built home is waiting for the new owners to further enhance the property with little effort. Upon entry you will be greeted with a sun drenched spacious living room flowing through to a well equipped kitchen and meals area. 3 generous sized bedrooms with robes serviced by a family bathroom and separate toilet. A large 2nd living area can also be found to the rear of the property as well as an oversized laundry. Underneath the carpet you will find beautiful hardwood floors just waiting to be exposed.
Outdoors offers a single remote garage, single carport, 2 garden sheds, and a storage shed on an approx. 680sqm block.
This well positioned home is walking distance to public transport, local schools, sporting grounds and Bellarine Village Shopping Centre.
Rental projection is $280-$300pw.
